version_description: The other two versions of this have several things wrong with them.  They are both missing a few chords, neither one has the Gmaj7,  the bridge is off on both, and Version 2 only tabbed half the song.

In the original version (which you can listen to at www.youtube.com/watch?v=sECAEAqshz0), Jason Mraz plays a G to a Gmaj7 in the chorus, but I think it sounds better to play a D in place of the Gmaj7, which is why I put (D) after the Gmaj7. I also wrote out the chords without the lyrics at the very bottom.
The Em is an E7, several chords are missing from the other versions.
